name: Verde at Babcock Ranch
description:
ABOUT THE HOME ENERGY RATING SCALE
The HERS (Home Energy Rating System) Index allows buyers to compare the relative energy efficiency of different homes. The HERS Index home energy rating is determined by an independent RESNET-certified home energy rater ("Rater"). The lower a home’s score, the more energy efficient it is in comparison to the HERS referenced home. For every one-point decrease in the HERS Index score, there is a corresponding one percent (1%) reduction in energy consumption as compared to a home with a HERS Index of 100. A home with a HERS score of 100 reflects a home built to 2006 IEEC Building Codes. See the bottom of this page for more information on HERS scores.

amenities.name: Within Midtown
amenities.description: Within Midtown which offers residents a new central gathering space: a next-generation, mixed-use town center with dining, offices, and shops.

amenities.name: Square Footage
amenities.description: 1 mile to Founder's Square featuring Slater's Goods & Provisions, Square Scoops, Lake House Kitchen, and more.

amenities.name: Nearby Jack
amenities.description: Nearby Jack Peeples Park, which includes 6 tennis courts, 4 pickleball courts, 2 bocce courts, and an open sports field.

amenities.name: Square Footage
amenities.description: Quick access to WellWay full service health club, which includes childcare, a 6-lane saltwater pool, weight room, pilate & cardio studios, fitness classes, massage therapy, and Lee Health offering occupational & physical therapy - located at Founder's Square.

amenities.name: miles Crescent
amenities.description: 2.5 miles from Crescent B Commons offering Taco Tuesdays and DJ nights at M’Xuma. Pizza and Karaoke nights at Pi Local. Pet Supermarket, The Royal Paw Grooming and The Animal Hospital at Babcock. Great Clips, Fiore & Ela Salon and Clover Nails for your beauty needs. Kumon Learning Center offering additional education. Starbucks, Fifth Third Bank, Babcock Dentist and so much more.

amenities.name: Home Designs
amenities.description: 2.5 miles to The Shoppes at Yellow Pine featuring a Marshalls, Ace Hardware, Aesthetics Lounge & Spa, Boujee Nail Bar, Carvel Ice Cream, Five Below, Five Guys, Fountain Pools, HomeGoods, Hope Chiropractic, Jersey Mike’s, Marshalls, Oar & Iron Raw Bar & Grill, Panera Bread, Papa Johns, Seymour Orthodontics, TGH Urgent Care, TGH Medical Center, Ulta Beauty, Verizon, and Yummy Express. Enjoy outdoor dining and gathering areas overlooking Sunset Lake.

amenities.name: Spend day
amenities.description: Spend the day at Cypress Lodge which features a huge swimming pool, a game lawn, and a clubhouse along with a 150ft boardwalk, floating dock and iconic Innovation Tower.

amenities.name: Host friends
amenities.description: Host friends and family at the Lake House in Lake Timber. This 2,400 sq. ft. Lakehouse features a zero-entry pool, play ground and overlooks Lake Timber.

amenities.name: water sports
amenities.description: If water sports are your preferred way of being outdoorsy, then skip the trails, grab a kayak or canoe and meet us on Lake Babcock.

amenities.name: Less than
amenities.description: Less than 10 miles to Publix Super Market at The Shops at Verandah

amenities.name: minutes Fort
amenities.description: 25 minutes to Fort Myers River District, offering restaurants, boutique shops, and tons of events and attractions

amenities.name: minutes Edison
amenities.description: 25 minutes to Edison Mall, including a wide variety of department and sporting goods stores, and Edison Park movie theater

amenities.name: Home Designs
amenities.description: 20 minutes to The Forum shopping plaza, including Target, Home Depot, Bed Bath & Beyond, Petco, and more

amenities.name: Verde perfect
amenities.description: Verde is the perfect community location in Midtown of Babcock Ranch. Just steps away from the amazing parks that Babcock Ranch has to offer!

amenities.name: Over 50%
amenities.description: Over 50% of Babcock Ranch is dedicated to greenways, parks, and nature paths, with a variety of outdoor spaces that facilitate an active lifestyle

amenities.name: New! Curry
amenities.description: New! Curry Creek linear Parks will meander along 3.5 miles, integrating six smaller parks — such as Blue Bird Park, Treehouse Point, Hillcrest Park, The Lagoon, Explorers Park, Bark Park and Palmetto Park — that offer themed play spaces, a favorite fishing hole, native plant trails, pavilions and picnic tables and lawns for sports and community wide events.

amenities.name: Jack Peeples
amenities.description: Jack Peeples Park featuring six tennis courts, four pickleball courts, a full basketball court, and two bocce ball courts, soccer field and playground.

amenities.name: Square Footage
amenities.description: Bullhorn Park and Sunset Park conveniently located just outside of Founders Square providing walking paths along with over 40 miles of community, recreation and greenway walking trails throughout Babcock Ranch.

amenities.name: Grand Opening!
amenities.description: Grand Opening! Near William and Mary Ann Smith Sports Complex, a outdoor sports facility offering a trailhead to Bill Hammond Trails, the sports complex offers softball, baseball, soccer and multipurpose fields, a skate park, game night field, running track, expansive flex lawns and ample parking.

amenities.name: Become member
amenities.description: Become a member of the Parks & Recreation Program that offers open gym access, various camps, amenity rentals and special members only events.

amenities.name: Gated community
amenities.description: Gated community with 399 future front doors

amenities.name: Nearby Bloom
amenities.description: Nearby Bloom Academy providing childcare and Babcock K-12 Neighborhood Charter Schools with onsite campus.

amenities.name: Stories
amenities.description: Life Tested®, consumer-inspired and innovative 1- and 2-story home designs

amenities.name: Private community
amenities.description: Private community amenities including a pool and pool cabana now open!

amenities.name: Smart home
amenities.description: Smart home technology

amenities.name: Town powered
amenities.description: Town powered entirely by the 75-megawatt Solar Energy Center

amenities.name: Adjacent 73,000
amenities.description: Adjacent to 73,000 acre Babcock Ranch Preserve

amenities.name: Florida Green
amenities.description: Florida Green Building Coalition (FGBC) certified town

amenities.name: New town
amenities.description: New town of 19,500 homes and 6 million sq. ft. of commercial space

amenities.name: Florida Green
amenities.description: Florida Green Building Coalition (FGBC) 2023 Builder of the Year for the most certified single-family homes
